<body>

  <h1>🎂 Birthday Surprise Website Documentation (Vercel + Firestore Chunking)</h1>
  <p>This document details the architecture, technical stack, user workflows, folder structure, and deployment guidelines for the interactive Birthday Surprise Website built for <strong>SYAMA</strong>.</p>

  <div class="info-box">
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> This website is serverless and uses a customized Base64 Document Chunking System inside Cloud Firestore. Files of any size (up to the database free limits) are stored directly inside Firestore, avoiding the need for a Firebase Storage bucket and bypassing credit card verification requirements.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>🛠️ Technical Stack</h2>
  
  <h3>Frontend (User Interface)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>HTML5 &amp; CSS3 (Vanilla)</strong>: Custom layout modules, modern HSL blur blobs, responsive grids, and glassmorphic panels.</li>
    <li><strong>JavaScript (ES6 Modules)</strong>: Client-side routing, interactive states, time calculations, and direct database queries using the Firebase Web JS SDK.</li>
    <li><strong>HTML5 Canvas API</strong>: Powering the custom confetti particle animation system.</li>
    <li><strong>CSS Keyframe Animations</strong>: Directs balloon floating cycles, polaroid tilts, card scale-ups, and candle flame flickers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cloud Backend &amp; Database (Serverless)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Vercel (Hosting)</strong>: Serves static frontends with 100% uptime, instant loading speeds, and automatic SSL setup.</li>
    <li><strong>Firebase Firestore (Database)</strong>: Real-time Cloud NoSQL database storing configuration document states, memory document lists, and segmented file chunks.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📂 Folder Structure &amp; Layout</h2>
  <p>The project directory is structured as follows:</p>
  <pre>
birthday-website/
├── package.json             # Local server script configuration
├── server.js                # Core Node.js HTTP local static server (for local dev testing only)
└── public/                  # Static assets uploaded directly to Vercel
    ├── admin.html           # Administrator panel HTML
    ├── index.html           # Main landing page HTML
    ├── css/
    │   └── style.css        # Main CSS stylesheet
    ├── js/
    │   ├── firebase.js      # Firebase connection configuration settings
    │   ├── app.js           # Client script for countdown and cake clicks
    │   └── admin.js         # Editor client script connected to Firebase
  </pre>

  <h2>🔄 System Workflows</h2>

  <h3>1. Public User Experience (Friend's View)</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Lock Phase (Before September 7th)</strong>: Displays a premium countdown clock, a locked birthday present box, and the dynamic greeting <em>"Surprise for SYAMA"</em>. Colorful balloons float continuously in the background.</li>
    <li><strong>Celebration Screen (Unlocked)</strong>: Replaces the countdown screen. A customized header loads, background music autoplays, and a layered CSS birthday cake appears.</li>
    <li><strong>Cake Interaction</strong>: Clicking the cake blows out the candles (extinguishing flames and emitting smoke puffs), triggers a massive confetti explosion, and reveals a sealed birthday card letter and the Polaroid memories gallery below.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>2. Editor Dashboard Experience (/admin)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Authentication</strong>: Secure login form requiring passcode (Default: <code>1234</code>, checked in Firestore).</li>
    <li><strong>Config settings</strong>: Change target date, update friend's name, or update passcode directly in Firestore settings document.</li>
    <li><strong>Upload memories</strong>: Drag &amp; drop files (MP3/OGG/MP4/PNG/JPG). Uploads are converted into a Base64 string and uploaded to a subcollection in Firestore divided into 800KB chunks.</li>
    <li><strong>Media manager</strong>: List uploaded files, download and assemble chunks dynamically, or delete documents and all corresponding subcollection chunks from Firestore.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>☁️ Vercel + Firebase Cloud Deployment</h2>
  <p>Follow these steps to host the application online for free:</p>

  <h3>Step 1: Set Up Your Firebase Project</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <code>console.firebase.google.com</code> and register a free account.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Add Project</strong> and name it <code>syama-birthday-surprise</code>.</li>
    <li>Register a new Web App (web project setup) and copy your config keys.</li>
    <li>Open <code>public/js/firebase.js</code> and paste these keys in the config block.</li>
    <li>Enable **Cloud Firestore** in the left sidebar:
        <ul>
          <li>Click **Create Database**.</li>
          <li>Choose **Start in Test Mode** (this allows read/write access immediately, required for uploads).</li>
          <li>Go to the **Rules** tab, check that it allows read and write, and click **Publish**.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Step 2: Push Your Code to GitHub</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Push the project to your GitHub repository (already done automatically).</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Step 3: Deploy to Vercel</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Log into <code>vercel.com</code> and click <strong>Add Project</strong>.</li>
    <li>Select your GitHub repository.</li>
    <li>Configure the **Root Directory** field to <code>public</code> (this serves the public folder directly).</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Deploy</strong>. Your site is live!</li>
  </ol>

</body>
